cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper is primarily focused on network programmability and the implementation of in-network functions using eBPF in the Linux kernel. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the implementation of this framework in the Linux kernel, which falls under the category of cs.OS (Operating Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance overhead of running eBPF network functions, which could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of eBPF to implement network functions, which could be classified under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
